    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-10-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-10-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="98"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d98">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">659.1112/38a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Denmark (<persName corresp="#p_CJFB1" type="to"
                            >Coleman</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 20, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>32. A correspondent of the United States Chamber of Commerce reports
                    discrimination appears to have become intensified during British exhibition and
                    that American goods are being subjected to higher import duties than similar
                    British goods ordered at exhibition. Please investigate both statements and
                    report briefly by cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
